================================================================================
FOURIER ANALYSIS: Var(r_S) = f(ΣQ²)
================================================================================
Since r_S is the inverse DFT of Q_k:
  r_S(d) = m²/p + (1/p)Σ Q_k cos(2πkd/p) + correction
  Var(r_S) ~ ΣQ² / p² (up to constants)
  More uniform r_S ↔ smaller ΣQ² ↔ flatter Q spectrum ↔ more topology

This means: FLAT Q-SPECTRUM → MAXIMUM |chi_per|
This is a SPECTRAL-TOPOLOGICAL DUALITY!
  - Paley (flat Q) → max |chi_per| at p≡3 mod 4
  - Quasi-Paley (nearly flat Q) → max |chi_per| at p≡1 mod 4
  - Interval (peaked Q) → min |chi_per| ≈ 0 or 1

  Verification across primes:
    p=7: S=[4, 5, 6]                 ΣQ²=    26.0 chi_per=   0
    p=7: S=[1, 2, 4]                 ΣQ²=    12.0 chi_per=   1
